Alameda County Library Homepage

Highlights

Highlights

Back to School eResources

With eResources such as ABCMouse, Beanstack, and much more, AC Library is here to help your student get school-ready!

School Up! Seminar: Beyond HS

Learn academic tips on high school success, choosing majors, thriving in college, networking, & building extracurriculars.

Honoring Our Shared Humanity

Join the Eden Area Interfaith Council, ING, & Castro Valley Library for a discussion on unity and combating Islamophobia & antisemitism.

Youth & Families

Explore resources, events, and activities that spark curiosity and joy!

Single Button Module

VIEW LATEST , opens a new window

Title Tracks

A reading list for teens. What's not to love when books and music blend together?

Climate-Fiction for Tweens

Cli-fi tackles climate change and global warming. These books may take place in a world we know or in the near future!

New Comics and Manga

For ages ranging from adult to children, these titles were all published or translated into English within the last two years.

Adults & Seniors

Discover something new, from author visits, career support, learning new languages, and more!

Single Button Module

VIEW LATEST , opens a new window

BlueCareer

Easy-to-use resource center for users interested in learning more about the skilled trades and seeking to explore a career transition.

Pre-Code Films

The Hays Code was a set of film industry guidelines that were enforced in 1934. Before this date things were rather more...free-wheeling.

Read by the Author

Don't miss out on the bonus comments when authors read their own work!

Support the Library

Your contributions to the library help us support and strengthen our communities!
